FBIS4-29171 "dreas116__a94007" FBIS-EAS-94-116-A Daily Report 15 Jun 1994 ANNEX Japan Continued Reportage on Reaction to DPRK Issues Continued Reportage on Reaction to DPRK Issues Kumagai Negative on U.S.-DPRK Talks OW1606081794 Tokyo MAINICHI SHIMBUN in Japanese 15 Jun 94 Evening Edition p 4 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY OW1606081794 Tokyo MAINICHI SHIMBUN Japanese BFN [Text] It is speculated that talks may possibly be held between the United states and the DPRK (North Korea) around late June on DPRK's suspected nuclear development. Regarding this speculation, Chief Cabinet Secretary Hiroshi Kumagai indicated his negative view at a news conference held on the morning of 15 June, and said: "Judging from the developments so far and the U.S. position, it is difficult to imagine that such talks will be held unless DPRK meets the demands of the international community."
